*What participants will do*
- Review 10 short HTML code samples (~100-200 lines each)
- Rate each sample on accessibility, effort-to-fix, and production-readines=
s
- Optionally describe any issues you notice
- Share overall impressions

*Details*
- Time: 30-45 minutes, self-paced
- Format: Single HTML page opened in your browser (fully accessible, 0
axe-core violations)
- Screen readers: JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver, or Orca - use whichever you prefer
- Compensation: up to 50 USD
- Privacy: All responses are anonymized. No personal data is stored beyond
what you provide.

*Who we're looking for*
- Blind or low-vision, with lived experience using a desktop screen reader
daily.
- At least 1 year of web development or accessibility-auditing experience.
- Comfortable reading and critiquing HTML/CSS/JavaScript.
- Able to screen record your session (audio + screen) and submit the JSON
output.

